<TITLE> Manikganj road accident leaves 1 killed, 20 injured </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Manikganj, June 27 (bdnews24.com) - A one year old baby was killed and 20 other people injured Wednesday morning in a road accident at Barongail on Dhaka-Aricha highway, police said. The victim was identified as Sakib, son of Abdul Malek of Vatbaur village under sadar upazila in Manikganj. Shahanaj Begum, 35, mother of Sakib, was among the 20 people injured in the accident. The rest of the injured could not be identified immediately. Abdul Hamid, Shibaloy police chief told bdnews24.com that the accident occurred at 8:45 am when a Dhaka bound passenger bus of Jatri Paribahan rammed into another standing bus of the same fleet from behind at Barongail bus stand. Police seized the errant bus but its driver and the helper, however, fled the scene. A case was filed with Shibalay police station in this connection. Five of the injured including Shahanaj Begum were rushed to Manikganj Sadar hospital. bdnews24
